        h3 About
        | SpriteBreaker is an open source browser based sprite management tool build by 
        a(href="" style="white-space:nowrap") Wilfred Godfrey
        |. SpriteBreaker aims to make managing and updating spritesheets as easy as possible.

        
        hr
        h4 Workflow guide
        ol

          li Load a fresh spritesheet using the 
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-folder-open
            |  &nbsp;New button

          li Add and name a new sprite 
            code eg "mario"

          li Add and name a new action 
            code eg "stand"

          li Add a new frame ( 
            kbd f
            |  on the keyboard)

          li Set your view area
            ul
              li Scroll and click/drag on the small canvas to set the view area

          li Set frame coordinates
            ul
              li Left click/drag on the large canvas to set the top left frame coordinates
              li Right click/drag on the large canvas to set the bottom right frame coordinates
          
          li Save your spritesheet, options and list with the 
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-floppy-disk
            | &nbsp;Save button

          li Copy the resulting JSON from the  
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-circle-arrow-down
            | &nbsp;Output area into your project

        hr
        h4 Good to know
        ul
          li You can change the output fomat in the options dialog (the 
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-cog
            |  button)

          li Load and delete saved spritesheets with the 
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-open
            | &nbsp;Load dialog

          li Update your current spritesheet with the 
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-repeat
            | &nbsp;Update button. You'll need to select this again every time you start the application (Browser security reasons).
        hr
        .alert.alert-info
          | Because SpriteBreaker makes use of the latest web standards, people using older browsers may run into problems. Then again, not sure why anyone with a crappy browser would even be interested in this.


      .modal-footer
        button.btn.btn-default(type='button' ng-click='$parent.$parent.$parent.infoOpen = false') Close
